      <div class="msgContentFrame"><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">alanwest09872 wrote:</div><div class="orig">I am an armor smithing level 11 and I cant make bronze ignot's. Everytime I try to make them it fails over and over again. its very frustrating. <br /> <br />also. How is it you get + 1 gear. i made nuggets at 400 quality and bam still not a + 1 2 or 3 item. how high do you have to get it anyways.</div></div> <br /> <br />You have to start reading, guy.  We've been over this.  It says right in the final window (the same one where it tells you what shards are required) if you should have a particular support buff for a recipe.  In the case if Bronze Ingots, you're going to want Common Armorer's Forge buff or you're probably going to fail. <br /> <br />Higher quality <b>increases</b> your chances of an HQ yield, but nothing <b>guarantees</b> an HQ.</div>
